For the algebraic generalization, see [Derivation (differential algebra)](/Derivation_(differential_algebra)). For other uses, see [Derivative (disambiguation)](/Derivative_(disambiguation)).

The [graph of a function](/Graph_of_a_function), depicted in black, showcases a [tangent line](/Tangent_line) rendered in red. The [slope](/Slope) of this tangent line precisely mirrors the derivative of the function at the indicated point. It's the sharpest linear approximation we can get for the function's behavior in the immediate vicinity.

The derivative at various points of a function that is differentiable everywhere. In this particular instance, the derivative is calculated as:

$$ \sin(x^2) + 2x^2 \cos(x^2) $$

